Quickstrike:






The wires shocked Quickstrike, taking his energy and shutting down some of 
his systems. He kept screaming and tried to struggle away. At the corner of 
his optics, when he opened them, he saw the scrap metal move. Streams of 
electric moved through the pieces and connected to each other. The parts 
formed into rough looking legs, and a head took shape.
